.nh
.TH uki-btrfs-snapshots 1
.SH NAME
uki-btrfs-snapshots \- Clone UKIs per btrfs snapshot with snapshot-rooted cmdlines

.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBuki-btrfs-snapshots\fP [\fIglobal options\fP] \fICOMMAND\fP [\fIargs\fP]

.SH DESCRIPTION
Discover btrfs snapshots and write one cloned UKI per (snapshot ×
source UKI) under uki.output_dir, each carrying a .cmdline section that
points at the snapshot's subvolume.

.PP
Use this only if your boot path is UKI-only (systemd-boot or direct
EFI Boot Manager entries pointing at /EFI/Linux/*.efi). Systems
booting via rEFInd or via BLS Type #1 entries don't need it — see
refind-btrfs-snapshots or bls-btrfs-snapshots instead.

.SH GLOBAL OPTIONS
.EX
  -c, --config string      Path to config file (default: /etc/uki-btrfs-snapshots.yaml)
      --log-level string   Log verbosity: trace, debug, info, warn, error
.EE

.SH COMMANDS
.SS uki-btrfs-snapshots generate
Clone UKIs per btrfs snapshot under uki.output_dir

.PP
\fBUsage:\fP \fBuki-btrfs-snapshots generate [flags]\fR

.PP
\fBOptions:\fP

.EX
      --dry-run   Show what would be written without making changes
      --force     Force generation even if booted from a snapshot
  -y, --yes       Automatically approve all changes without prompting
.EE

.SS uki-btrfs-snapshots version
Print version information

.PP
\fBUsage:\fP \fBuki-btrfs-snapshots version\fR
